issue.title: Add percentile method for PTQ

issue.body:
**Description**:  Add percentile method for PTQ.

**Motivation and Context**
- Why is this change required? What problem does it solve?
BERT SQUAD QDQ model can achieve better accuracy if using percentile method to do the calibration.

body: Thanks for bringing out this issue. We will inspect it.

> do kl_divergence quant scale can work? i get big drop of acc

Yes, it can work.

Please note that the [code](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/master/onnxruntime/python/tools/quantization/calibrate.py#L570) `num_bins = hist.size`  is not always 128 even though we explicitly set num_quantized_bins to 128.
The reason is that the range of tensor value's histogram might expand during histogram merging ([here](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/master/onnxruntime/python/tools/quantization/calibrate.py#L514)) which depends on the tensor value data the collector collects.
However, we will make num_bins and num_quantized_bins configurable in another PR and you can set different num_bins and num_quantized_bins to see whether it can achieve better accuracy.

issue.body:
Make 'num_bins', 'num_quantized_bin' and 'percentile' configurable for entropy and percentile calibration algorithm so that users can fine-tune the calibration for their models.

Please see the issue discussion here: https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/9597

body: The PR https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/pull/10204 now can make 'num_bins', 'num_quantized_bin' and 'percentile' configurable
